column633: I am not really sure how the data is analyzed because genders, ages, and generations really differentiate the Hispanic/Latino culture.

A concern that I have about this study is that Hispanic men and women are drastically different. Thus, I had to put 4 on a lot of my answers because I couldn't necessarily let one side outweigh the other. When I say that they're different, I mean that their roles aren't similar in the sense that the man is typically the provider while the woman is the maintainer. Consequently, when asked about words like "warm-hearted," I could easily say that the women are while men aren't.
Do I receive recognition for this study?
None that I can think of.
Interesting study, but a bit too much questions.
My only comment is that this took me about an hour and a half to complete rather than an hour.
Thank you for allowing me to be apart of this study it was very interesting.
